Western media sources are now erroneously reporting that Kim Jong Un did 
not have his own uncle executed by a pack of starved dogs, but I know the 
truth, and I can no longer harbor, or bear the weight of this ugly truth, 
that I witnessed first hand. Please read on.

I recently returned from North Korea (I plead the Fifth as to which 
organization granted me access), and was one of thirteen people allowed to 
view the execution proceedings of Kim Jong Un's uncle. The kennel that I 
was driven to was rank-smelling. A horrible mixture of dried urine and 
feces. Jang Song Thaek, Un’s uncle, was was led in to the kennel area by 
two guards, his head covered by a black sack, metal shackles bound both his 
wrists and ankles. He was screaming from under the sack as they led him 
over to a large pit, but I do not speak Korean, so I have no clue as to 
what he said. The pit looked like a large dinner bowl made of cement. I 
imagine it was forty feet in diameter and fifteen feet deep at the rim. At 
the far end of the pit was a green gate. Kim Jong Un lifted a finger and 
then, lazily, ran it under his own throat. With that small gesture, one of 
the guards pushed Jang into the pit. He managed to get the sack off, but 
the gate was already coming up. It was horrifying to watch all of those 
dogs race in. All that barking. The pack was a mixed breed, but they were 
all large and unkempt looking. Jang started hopping towards us, but the 
dogs were too quick. For respect of the dead, I will not describe the 
horrific events that I saw transpire inside the confines of that wicked 
cement pit. But I will tell you that what Kim Jong Un did while the 
travesty ensued was equally horrid. Un signaled over to another guard and 
instantly loud music began to blast from a series of speakers hung over the 
pit. Then Un lifted a microphone and began to sing ‘Who Let The Dogs Out?’ 
at the top of his lungs, to his uncle, dancing around the pit, pumping his 
fist up with every ‘Whoop, Whoop!’ …We must do something about this manic.﻿
